  "prompt": "I did really bad on my 1st term of 11th (cbse).If I pull myself together and do really well on the other 2 terms can I still get above 95% at the end?",
  "response": "Yes, it is definitely possible to achieve an overall percentage above 95% even if you didn't perform well in your first term. The CBSE system typically evaluates your final grade based on the combined scores of all three terms, so you can still significantly improve your overall percentage with strong performances in your remaining terms.\n\nHere are some steps to help you maximize your scores for the rest of the year:\n\n1. **Assess Your Performance**: Identify the subjects and topics where you struggled in the first term. Understanding your weaknesses will allow you to focus your efforts effectively.\n\n2. **Create a Study Plan**: Develop a structured study plan that allocates time for each subject. Ensure that you cover the entire syllabus and allocate extra time to challenging subjects.\n\n3. **Practice Regularly**: Use past papers, sample papers, and additional resources to practice. This helps you get familiar with the exam format and question types.\n\n4. **Seek Help When Needed**: Don\u2019t hesitate to ask teachers or classmates for help if you're struggling with certain concepts.\n\n5. **Stay Consistent**: Regular study and revision will reinforce your learning. Try to maintain a steady pace to avoid cramming before the exams.\n\n6. **Focus on Board Exam Patterns**: Understand the exam patterns and marking schemes to prioritize your study efforts accordingly.\n\n7. **Take Care of Yourself**: Make sure to balance your studies with rest and wellness. Good physical and mental health are crucial for effective studying.\n\nIf you commit to your studies and follow a disciplined routine, there's a strong chance you can improve your scores in the next two terms and achieve your goal of a 95% overall percentage. Good luck!",
